Hi,

My demo application leaks about 100Kb every 20 seconds on real device. I thought that it could be because of garbage collector, but I waited during 20 minutes.

Here are my steps:
1. I used Cocos.app v 3.10. I created new JS project with precompiled libraries.
2. I added the code to create new sprite, move it, remove from parent and do all in a loop.
3. When I run the app the memory was 25.1Mb. It grown to 27.2Mb during 6 minutes of testing.
4. After 20 minutes, the memory was 31Mb.

![screen shot 2016-03-22 at 11 21 00 am](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6491282/13946003/c47d948e-f022-11e5-977f-b53d6397a29f.png)

Here are my changes (use any .png 64x64):

```
var HelloWorldScene = cc.Scene.extend({
    onEnter:function () {
        this._super();
        var layer = new HelloWorldLayer();
        this.addChild(layer);
        for (var i = 0; i < 10; i++)
            this.addsprite(70*i);
    },
    addsprite: function(posy) {
        var sprite = new cc.Sprite(res.Sprite_png);
        var size = cc.winSize;

        sprite.setPosition(40, posy);
        sprite.runAction(cc.sequence(
                cc.moveTo(0.5, cc.p(size.width-40, posy)),
                cc.callFunc(this.delsprite, this, sprite)
                ));
        this.addChild(sprite);
    },
    delsprite: function(sprite) {
        sprite.stopAllActions();
        var posy = sprite.getPositionY();
        sprite.removeFromParent(true);
        this.addsprite(posy);
    }
});
```

BTW. In my other application, I tried use cache and not to create/remove sprite. This did not help. The app still leaked.
